reviews.review: A fine wrap up to the Skywalker Saga.  Rights many of the wrongs of the Last Jedi, which is by far the worst film in the entire franchise (Holiday Special, Ewok movies and prequels included). It's a fun ride the whole way through.  Not without several "Well how the hell did that happen?" moments but, suspend disbelief and remember it's a Star Wars film and is a space fantasy film for the whole family with crazy creatures/aliens and locations where good is supposed to triumph over evil in a galaxy far, far, away as long as there is heart.  This film has heart and is a good sci-fi adventure which is all I wanted.  Left the theatre feeling good and not sick like I did with episode 8.  Best movie of this trilogy!
Predictable plotting and messy script erratic and frantic pacing. Episode 9 is without question the weakest of the serial films.
Great movie I will see again
One of the worst paced movies I've ever seen.
I'm a Star Wars fan and I thought this one was just ok. The story sometimes dragged and it seemed a bit long. I like that they paid tribute to Princess Leia (the Carrie Fisher role).

I had low expectations going to see this movie based on episode 7 and 8, but was pleasantly surprised how much I like this last episode. It was entertaining and tied it all together nicely. Everyone in our group of 7 loved it. Don't try to analyze it too much and just enjoy. =)
Loved it but they need to work on the projector in this IMAX laser, it was too dim. Watched it a few days later in Dolby in Houston and the opening scenes were not as dim
A few plot holes but still a joyride like few others.  A satisfying completion to a nine-film epic.

This movie reminds me of a 1st grade kids art project-- sure its fun and you like it, but not 2.5 hours worth.
